## 19. Foundation Drainage

- Site drainage risk: {{ site.drainage_risk }}.
- Foundation drainage should consider uphill interception, perimeter drains, waterproofing protection, capillary breaks, frost protection, discharge location, cleanouts, and inspection points.
- Final strategy depends on geotechnical investigation, groundwater, soil permeability, slope stability, and civil/structural coordination.

## 20. Maintenance Checklist

- Keep shutoff valves, filters, pumps, pressure vessels, tanks, drains, cleanouts, inspection chambers, treatment equipment, and terrace drains accessible.
- Confirm winter drain-down procedure for exterior taps, terrace plumbing, optional tank lines, and vacant-period systems.
- Schedule periodic cleaning for gutters, terrace drains, floor drains, traps, filters, septic/treatment equipment, and tank access points.
- Maintain records of inspections, pump service, wastewater servicing, water quality checks, and frost incidents.

## 21. Licensed Plumbing/Mechanical Review Checklist

- Confirm mains water or tank supply strategy, pressure, flow, treatment, filtration, and backflow protection.
- Confirm final pipe sizing, material selection, insulation, supports, penetrations, isolation valves, and commissioning tests.
- Confirm hot-water source, cylinder, expansion, safety discharge, scald protection, legionella controls, and maintenance clearances.
- Confirm sanitary drainage, slopes, venting, traps, cleanouts, inspection chambers, wastewater treatment, and authority approvals.
- Confirm rainwater, terrace, and foundation drainage against frost, slope, erosion, waterproofing, and maintenance access.
- Confirm that this document remains PRELIMINARY and does not claim local wastewater approval or final pipe sizing.

